Legal Calculus 4.5 — Tier 6: Procedural Sovereignty — Module 67
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 67

Mandate & Remand — Implementing Appellate Instructions

⚖️ Core Message

When the mandate drops, execute quickly and accurately; the record is watching.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Read the mandate and opinion for precise scope; list tasks and deadlines.
2. File a 'Notice of Mandate and Implementation Plan' with a short schedule.
3. If scope is disputed, request a status conference with targeted questions.
4. Update the archive and index with mandate-specific entries.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 'Notice of Mandate and Implementation Plan' with three tasks and dates.
✅ Model Response

NOTICE OF MANDATE (excerpt)

1. Task: enter findings on element X by [date].

2. Task: re-open limited discovery on Y by [date].

3. Task: set 15-minute status conference within 10 days.

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Execution is part of persuasion.
🎨 Visual Concept

An envelope stamped 'MANDATE' feeding a checklist printer.
